    <title>Build personal blog on Mac using hexo</title>
    <link href="http://yoursite.com/2017/12/02/Build-personal-blog-on-Mac-using-hexo/"/>
    <id>http://yoursite.com/2017/12/02/Build-personal-blog-on-Mac-using-hexo/</id>
    <published>2017-12-02T19:06:02.000Z</published>
    <updated>2017-12-02T21:36:41.000Z</updated>
    
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<h2 id="github-preparation"><a href="#github-preparation" class="headerlink" title="github preparation"></a>github preparation</h2><ol><li>make sure you have github account and create a repository with name <code>[your github name].github.io</code>. For example, if my github account is <code>amy</code>, the created github repository should be <code>amy.github.io</code>.</li><li>add a ssh key to your github account. First check whether a ssh key exists on your Mac.<pre><code>ls -al ~/.ssh</code></pre>If you donâ€™t have one on your Mac, create one using the following command.<pre><code>ssh-keygen -t rsa -C your_email@example.com</code></pre></li><li>add the generated ssh key to your github. <code>settings -&gt; ssh and gpg keys -&gt; new ssh key</code></li></ol><h2 id="hexo-preparation"><a href="#hexo-preparation" class="headerlink" title="hexo preparation"></a>hexo preparation</h2><ol><li>install <a href="https://hexo.io/docs/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">hexo</a></li><li><p>create a folder as the root diretory of your blog, e.g.</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> ~</span><br><span class="line">mkdir blog</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p>initiate the root directory, i.e.</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line"><span class="built_in">cd</span> blog</span><br><span class="line">hexo init</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p>install some dependencies</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">npm install hexo --save</span><br><span class="line">npm install hexo-deployer-git --save</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure></li><li><p>(optional) run a hexo server to preview. <code>hexo s</code>. Preview your blog at <a href="http://localhost:4000" target="_blank" rel="noopener">http://localhost:4000</a></p></li><li><p>modify the _config.yml in the <code>blog</code> directory. On the last line of the file (deploy section), makes it look like</p><figure class="highlight bash"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre><span class="line">1</span><br><span class="line">2</span><br><span class="line">3</span><br><span class="line">4</span><br></pre></td><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">deploy:</span><br><span class="line">    <span class="built_in">type</span>: git</span><br><span class="line">    repo: url of the repository.</span><br><span class="line">    branch: master</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure><p> Remember the repository you just created? Copy its url and put it on the repo line.</p></li><li>run the command <code>hexo generate</code> to generate your blog.</li><li>run the command <code>hexo deploy</code> to deploy your blog.</li><li>visit the website <a href="https://amy.github.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">https://amy.github.io</a> and enjoy your new blog!!</li></ol>]]></content>
    
